data: {"item_id":"rs_7b4d9fdb5ade0e2296429392","output_index":0,"sequence_number":122,"summary_index":0,"text":"**Explaining prime properties**\n\nI’m starting from the idea that primes greater than 3 are either ±1 mod 6. I need to see if their squares are ≡1 mod 24. Looking at (6k ± 1)², I can see it expands to 36k² ± 12k + 1. Now, I need to show 12k(3k ± 1) is divisible by 24. If k is even, 12k is clearly divisible, and if k is odd, then 3k ± 1 is even, making it work too. I’ll keep it stepwise and finish with a concise conclusion.","type":"response.reasoning_summary_text.done"}

