data: {"response":{"background":false,"completed_at":1776601606,"created_at":1776601595,"error":null,"frequency_penalty":0,"id":"resp_827bc1b24cb12ee06b0d6855","incomplete_details":null,"instructions":null,"max_output_tokens":4096,"max_tool_calls":null,"metadata":{},"model":"gpt-5.4-2026-03-05","object":"response","output":[{"encrypted_content":"","id":"rs_7b4d9fdb5ade0e2296429392","summary":[{"text":"**Explaining prime properties**\n\nI’m starting from the idea that primes greater than 3 are either ±1 mod 6. I need to see if their squares are ≡1 mod 24. Looking at (6k ± 1)², I can see it expands to 36k² ± 12k + 1. Now, I need to show 12k(3k ± 1) is divisible by 24. If k is even, 12k is clearly divisible, and if k is odd, then 3k ± 1 is even, making it work too. I’ll keep it stepwise and finish with a concise conclusion.","type":"summary_text"}],"type":"reasoning"},{"content":[{"annotations":[],"logprobs":[],"text":"Here is a short, clean proof.\n\n1. Since \\(p>3\\) is prime, \\(p\\) is not divisible by \\(2\\) or \\(3\\).\n\n2. Because \\(p\\) is not divisible by \\(2\\), it is odd.  \n   Any odd integer can be written as \\(p=2k+1\\). Then\n   \\[\n   p^2=(2k+1)^2=4k^2+4k+1=4k(k+1)+1.\n   \\]\n   Since \\(k\\) and \\(k+1\\) are consecutive, one of them is even, so \\(k(k+1)\\) is even. Hence \\(4k(k+1)\\) is divisible by \\(8\\), and therefore\n   \\[\n   p^2 \\equiv 1 \\pmod{8}.\n   \\]\n\n3. Because \\(p\\) is not divisible by \\(3\\), we must have\n   \\[\n   p \\equiv 1 \\text{ or } 2 \\pmod{3}.\n   \\]\n   Squaring either possibility gives\n   \\[\n   p^2 \\equiv 1^2 \\equiv 1 \\pmod{3}\n   \\quad\\text{or}\\quad\n   p^2 \\equiv 2^2=4 \\equiv 1 \\pmod{3}.\n   \\]\n   So in all cases,\n   \\[\n   p^2 \\equiv 1 \\pmod{3}.\n   \\]\n\n4. Now \\(p^2-1\\) is divisible by both \\(8\\) and \\(3\\). Since \\(\\gcd(8,3)=1\\), it must be divisible by\n   \\[\n   8\\cdot 3=24.\n   \\]\n   Thus\n   \\[\n   p^2 \\equiv 1 \\pmod{24}.\n   \\]\n\nTherefore, for every prime \\(p>3\\), \\(\\boxed{p^2 \\equiv 1 \\pmod{24}}\\).","type":"output_text"}],"id":"msg_1b14dd340400c2f166b86857","phase":"final_answer","role":"assistant","status":"completed","type":"message"}],"parallel_tool_calls":true,"presence_penalty":0,"previous_response_id":null,"prompt_cache_retention":"in_memory","reasoning":{"effort":"high","summary":"detailed"},"safety_identifier":"6b0c592b6b72fe358a8fed20b67212a1f137fd41b46f163fe37453dbb1c9f7ae","service_tier":"default","status":"completed","store":false,"temperature":1,"text":{"format":{"type":"text"},"verbosity":"medium"},"tool_choice":"auto","tools":[],"top_logprobs":0,"top_p":0.98,"truncation":"disabled","usage":{"input_tokens":42,"input_tokens_details":{"cached_tokens":0},"output_tokens":845,"output_tokens_details":{"reasoning_tokens":399},"total_tokens":887},"user":null},"sequence_number":570,"type":"response.completed"}

